text:
This is pretty cool. Today 4/22, is Earth Day. So Origins sent me this gift box
with a Sprout ✏️ which I have never seen before. You can use the pencil, and
then plant it when you are done. Add sunlight & water and it will sprout into a
new plant. Awesome 👏. Also got a reusable shopping bag and lunch box. Add in
some cool products and I’m a happy camper on Earth Day. 
🙏 @origins @originstaiwan 
❤️ 🌍 🌎 🌏 ❤️

Finished last nights year end party at 10pm, and by the time I got home, ate,
showered, and wrote today’s cue cards, it was almost 1am. Then got up at 6:20am
to catch the 7:30 train to Taichung. 9am rundown meeting, 10am final rehearsal,
11am lunch, 11:45 on stage. 3:30 finish. Rush back to Taipei. Eat. Shower. And
now I’m pooped. January is going to be brutal with all the year end parties, but
I’m ready for U. #漢微科#yearendparty #hmiyearendparty #6down @ Taichung, Taiwan

text:
If there really is a tree of life than I was fortunate enough to see it today up
high in the mountains of Hokkaido. I stopped snowboarding and had to turn back
when I saw this majestic tree 🌳. It called out to me, a symbol of growth,
beauty, and uniqueness. Just stare at it for a second. I hope u are able to feel
what I felt, a moment of serenity, an abundance of hope, a shot of joy and
happiness, a blissful optimism. 2019 has been a trying time, an exciting time,
an emotional time. But what I have learned is that life marches on and we must
move forward. Better yourself and your community, uplift your friends, and be
kind. Let go of things you have no control over, complain less, and do more. 
This shining white tree stood there in front of me, the sky hanging like a dark
blue curtain, and it grows...slowly it grows. This tree survives the harshest
winters, its leaves bloom every spring, it sings in the summer and wails in the
fall. It is resilient, it moves on as we must do ourselves. 
Jackie and I look forward to what I am sure will be an unforgettable 2020. We
wish to make fantastic memories with Ryder & Makayla. We want to smile, laugh,
and cry with our family and friends. And lastly we want to share these precious
moments with you. 
Thank you for your support. 
We love ❤️ you and thanks for being a part of our family tree,

 Alex 艾力克斯 & Jackie 李詠嫻
